    "page.faq.subsection.order.cancelled.answer": "If your order is cancelled by you or by Resto-in according to the restaurant, we won’t remove any money from your account.",
    "page.faq.subsection.order.phone": "Can I do my order by phone?",
    "page.faq.subsection.order.phone.answer1": "Yes. On the home page, you can find the customercare number or in the page contact.",
    "page.faq.subsection.order.phone.answer2": "We use a payment company to securely encrypt all transactions made through the site.",
    "page.faq.subsection.order.phone.answer3": "We also have a designated in-house team that may give you a call from time to time to verify your details – just as an extra security measure.",
    "page.faq.subsection.order.restoin": "How to order with Resto-in?",
    "page.faq.subsection.order.restoin.answer1": "Visit www.resto-in.com and enter in your zipcode. That zipode is then matched with local takeaways in your area. We show you a list of restaurant with description, menu, comments… and you can pick which what you want.",
    "page.faq.subsection.order.restoin.answer2": "Then browse their menu and do your choice. Then you can pay for your order with card or cash on delivery. We send that order to the restaurants, and they prepare your order.",
    "page.faq.subsection.pay.order": "How can I pay for my order?",
    "page.faq.subsection.pay.order.answer1": "Your options are pretty straight forward, cash on delivery/collection, or card payment. The cards we accept are MasterCard, Maestro, Visa Paypal and Amex.",
    "page.faq.subsection.pay.order.answer2": "Once you’ve finished selecting your food just select ‘Place My Order’. Then you’re on the payment screen, and you have two options. You can select pay by card, or by cash on the delivery. You can also save your card details for future orders.",
    "page.faq.subsection.placed.2.orders": "I think I placed 2 orders, 1 has gone through – I think I need a payment returned.",
    "page.faq.subsection.placed.2.orders.answer": "This may have happened if you closed your browser whilst payment was being processed. Just get in touch with our customer care, one agent will verify the problem.",
    "page.faq.subsection.preorder.food": "Can I pre-order my food for a specific time?",
    "page.faq.subsection.preorder.food.answer1": "Yes. The minimum delivery time for any restaurant is 45 minutes after your order has been placed. ",
    "page.faq.subsection.preorder.food.answer2": "To pre-order, just select the date and time you want your food delivered from the drop down menu before you actually place your order.",
    "page.faq.subsection.preorder.food.answer3": "If you don’t select a time, the order is delivered as soon as possible. The restaurant will confirm the exact time on your confirmation email once they have received the order.",
    "page.faq.subsection.preorder.food.answer4": "For few restaurants you have to do your order 24hours before the delivery",
    "page.faq.subsection.rate.food": "Can I rate my food?",
    "page.faq.subsection.rate.food.answer": "After your order, you’ll get an email asking you to rate your meal or you can log in to your account, find the order and leave a review anytime.",
    "page.faq.subsection.something.missing.order": "Something is missing in my order",
    "page.faq.subsection.something.missing.order.answer1": "If happens, you can:",
    "page.faq.subsection.something.missing.order.answer2": "Check your email confirmation to make sure your item was listed",
    "page.faq.subsection.something.missing.order.answer3": "Call the our customer service to find a solution and where does the problem comes from.",
    "page.faq.subsection.take.account.answer1": "When you select ‘Place my Order’, your bank checks your account to see if you have the funds available to make the order. Then they reserve the money for this transaction before it’s complete – the money is still in your account, just not in your available balance.",
